# =============================================================================
# Azure — resource groups & what to create (portal, Bicep, ARM, or Terraform)
# =============================================================================
#
# You typically use ONE resource group per environment (recommended):
#   • rg-build-connect-dev
#   • rg-build-connect-prod
#
# Alternatively, a single group for early pilots:
#   • rg-build-connect-sandbox
#
# Inside each resource group, create these Azure resources for this app:
#
# 1) App Service plan (Linux) + Web App
#    - Runtime: Node 20 LTS (or 18 LTS)
#    - Hosts the Next.js build from GitHub Actions → Azure App Service deploy
#
# 2) Azure Database for PostgreSQL — Flexible Server
#    - Engine: PostgreSQL 15+ (match your org policy)
#    - Networking: prefer private access + VNet integration for production
#    - Copy the connection string into DATABASE_URL below (use sslmode=require)
#
# 3) Storage account (Blob) — recommended in Azure (App Service disk is ephemeral)
#    - Private container for certification files; set AZURE_STORAGE_* below.
#    - Without Azure: uploads go to LOCAL_CERT_UPLOAD_DIR (default ./uploads/certs) — dev only.
#
# 4) Azure Communication Services — optional until you send email from the app
#    - For cert-expiry and match notifications (replaces generic SMTP if desired)
#
# 5) (Recommended) Azure Key Vault
#    - Store DATABASE_URL, NEXTAUTH_SECRET, OAuth secrets, storage keys
#    - Reference secrets from the Web App configuration (Key Vault references)
#
# 6) (Recommended) Application Insights
#    - Link to your Web App for logs and performance
#
# 7) GitHub Actions
#    - Deploy to the Web App in this resource group (OIDC to Azure or publish profile)
#    - Set repository secrets to match production/staging slot URLs and credentials
#
# Naming tip: keep region consistent (e.g. West US 2) for App Service + Postgres
# low latency between app and database.
#
# =============================================================================

# --- PostgreSQL (Azure Flexible Server or local) ---
# Local Docker (matches docker-compose.yml): npm run db:init
# postgresql://postgres:postgres@127.0.0.1:5432/buildconnect?schema=public
#
# Local Homebrew: brew install postgresql@16 && brew services start postgresql@16
# Put CLI on PATH: export PATH="/opt/homebrew/opt/postgresql@16/bin:$PATH"  (Apple Silicon)
# Create DB + role to match DATABASE_URL above, then: npx prisma db push && npm run db:seed
#
# Azure example (add sslmode=require):
# postgresql://APPUSER:PASSWORD@your-server.postgres.database.azure.com:5432/buildconnect?sslmode=require
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST:5432/buildconnect?schema=public"

# --- Next.js / NextAuth (public URL of your Web App) ---
# Local: http://localhost:3000
# Azure default: https://<your-webapp-name>.azurewebsites.net
# Custom domain: https://app.buildconnect.example.org
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=""
NEXTAUTH_URL="https://your-webapp-name.azurewebsites.net"

# --- Google OAuth (Azure: add authorized redirect URI) ---
# Redirect URI in Google Cloud Console:
#   https://<your-domain>/api/auth/callback/google
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=""
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=""

# --- Email: magic link (SMTP) OR Azure Communication Services later ---
# NextAuth Email provider (SMTP), e.g. smtp://user:pass@smtp.example.com:587
EMAIL_SERVER=""
EMAIL_FROM="Build Connect <noreply@example.com>"

# Azure Communication Services (use when you send mail from your own code, not NextAuth SMTP)
# AZURE_COMMUNICATION_CONNECTION_STRING="endpoint=https://....communication.azure.com/;accesskey=..."

# --- Certification file storage ---
# Production: Azure Blob (required on App Service — local disk is not durable)
# AZURE_STORAGE_CONNECTION_STRING=""   # from Storage account → Access keys
# AZURE_STORAGE_CONTAINER_CERTS="cert-uploads"   # container name (created on first upload if missing)
#
# Local / fallback (no Azure): files under this directory (gitignored by default)
# LOCAL_CERT_UPLOAD_DIR=""
# Portfolio photos (local fallback): defaults to ./uploads/portfolio
# LOCAL_PORTFOLIO_UPLOAD_DIR=""
#
# Optional legacy split (not used by cert upload code; connection string is enough):
# AZURE_STORAGE_ACCOUNT_NAME=""
# AZURE_STORAGE_ACCOUNT_KEY=""
# AZURE_STORAGE_CONTAINER_PROFILES="profile-photos"

# --- Observability (optional) ---
# APPLICATIONINSIGHTS_CONNECTION_STRING="InstrumentationKey=...;IngestionEndpoint=..."

# --- Twilio SMS (optional) — ping workers when they get an in-app message ---
# Requires User.phone (E.164 or 10-digit US). In-app chat works without Twilio.
# TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=""
# TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=""
# TWILIO_FROM_NUMBER=""   # your Twilio SMS-capable number, e.g. +15551234567

# --- Local development only ---
# Azure / production: "false" (required). Local machine: "true" only if you use seeded dev login.
DEV_AUTH_BYPASS="false"

# --- Optional: scripts / IaC / CI (not read by Next.js unless you use them) ---
# AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID=""
# AZURE_RESOURCE_GROUP="rg-build-connect-prod"
# AZURE_WEBAPP_NAME=""
